Saban Planning Bid for HIT Entertainment, Times of London Says

-- B y   C a r o l i n e   A l e x a n d e r
-- 
2011-04-03T09:20:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-03/saban-planning-bid-for-hit-entertainment-times-of-london-says.html
Saban Capital Group Chief Executive
Officer  Haim Saban  is preparing to bid for HIT Entertainment,
the owner of Thomas the Tank Engine and Bob the Builder, the
 Times of London  reported.  Saban is expected to compete with Hasbro Inc., Mattel Inc.,
Walt Disney Co., and former Disney boss Michael Eisner in the
700 million-pound auction ($1.1 million), the Times said. HIT
Entertainment is being sold by Apax Partners LLP, its private
equity owner, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Caroline Alexander in  London  at 
 calexander1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  